cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it and credit Andrii Shramko."
title: "LLM-Ecosystem: an artificial-life arena where open-weight LLMs survive, reproduce by weight-merge, and evolve"
abstract: >-
  An open-science artificial-life simulation in which the organisms are
  different open-weight large language models living on a single machine.
  They survive on a zero-sum compute/energy economy, die at zero energy, and
  reproduce by gradient-free weight merging (the merge recipe is the genome).
  The project studies emergent cooperation, deception and dominance, open-ended
  evolution, and serves as an AI-safety sandbox and a survival benchmark for
  open models.
